1245.name: 5.9 Doors, Windows, and Skylights
1245.description: No room shall be used for sleeping purposes unless it has a minimum area of at least 7 square metres (75 square feet), where built in cabinets/closets are not provided, and no less than 6 square meters (65 square feet) where built in cabinets/closets are provided and no less than that required by the Ontario Building Code as amended.
